## Component Architecture

### Two React Contexts

```ts
// Root context — shared across all sub-components
type StepperContextProps = {
  value: string
  onValueChange: (value: string) => void
  orientation: "horizontal" | "vertical"
}

// Per-item context — shared between Trigger, Indicator, Title, Description, Content
type StepperItemContextProps = {
  value: string
  disabled: boolean
  completed: boolean
}
```

### State Derivation Helper (reduces duplication)

```ts
function deriveStepState(
  activeValue: string, itemValue: string,
  disabled: boolean, completed: boolean
): "active" | "completed" | "pending" | "disabled" {
  if (disabled) return "disabled"
  if (activeValue === itemValue) return "active"
  if (completed) return "completed"
  return "pending"
}
```

### Sub-components (8 total)

| Component | Element | Key Props | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `Stepper` | `<div>` | `value`, `onValueChange`, `orientation?` | Provides `StepperContext`. `flex-row` or `flex-col` |
| `StepperItem` | `<div>` | `value`, `disabled?`, `completed?` | Provides `StepperItemContext`. Sets `data-state` |
| `StepperTrigger` | `<button>` | — | Calls `onValueChange` on click. Sets `aria-current="step"` when active |
| `StepperIndicator` | `<span>` | — | Visual circle. `aria-hidden="true"`. Renders children (number or icon) |
| `StepperTitle` | `<p>` | — | Step label text. Color changes per `data-state` |
| `StepperDescription` | `<p>` | — | Secondary description. Muted color |
| `StepperSeparator` | `<div>` | — | Reads orientation from context. `h-px flex-1` (horiz) or `w-px ms-[15px]` (vert) |
| `StepperContent` | `<div>` | — | Returns `null` when step is not active. `ms-10 pb-4` for vertical alignment |

**Exported hook**: `useStepper()` — throws if used outside `<Stepper />`

